Merge branch 'eyraud/154' into 'master'

[TGen] Fix translation of array types constrained by a subtype ...

Closes #154

See merge request eng/ide/libadalang-tools!197

[TGen] Fix translation of array types constrained by a subtype ...

... that itself has a constraint. TGen used to ignore the subtype
constraint, which resulted in generating values that were not compliant
to the array bounds, ultimately resulting in a crash.

Merge branch 'eyraud/153' into 'master'

[TGen] Fix interval size computation in floating point generation

Closes #153

See merge request eng/ide/libadalang-tools!196

[TGen] Fix interval size computation in floating point generation

When computing the number of floating point values in a given range, we
were including a spurious binade, which could result in generating a
floating point outside of the range.

Merge branch 'leo/151-array_limit' into 'master'

TGen: Add array size limit beyond which marshallers do not attempt to load them

Closes #151

See merge request eng/ide/libadalang-tools!192

TGen: Add array size limit beyond which marshallers do not attempt to load them

This safety net helps avoid out-of-memory errors by blindly allocating a huge
array from bounds read from the stream.

The limit defaults to 1000 (same size as the largest generated arrays),
but can be configured by setting the TGEN_ARRAY_LIMIT environment variable
for the command generating the marshallers.

Merge branch 'leo/152-robustify' into 'master'

Test.Stub: Robustify calls to LAL API

Closes #152

See merge request eng/ide/libadalang-tools!193

Use P_Designated_Type_Decl instead of our own in house helper

The LAL properties often account for more edge cases, and laltools
will also benefit from bug fixes reported by other teams this way.

Test.Stub: Robustify calls to LAL API

This change adds a fallback in case of property errors when determining
if a parameter type is definite or not. As we have a safe default, only
warn in such cases.
